    <description>This is the 2nd installment for the Napoleon's Battles miniatures Rules set. There are 5 additional Scenarios as well as Updated 'Errata' and clarifications for the previously released Game and 1st Module. There are 'New' concepts introduced which includes those such as 'Unknown' Tabletop Terrain Markers, the 'Campaign' Game and even some 'fast' Campaigns. With even some more Additional Optional Rules, an Expanded General Ratings Information chart, additional labels for the Scenarios included, a 'sheet' of Unknown Terrain Markers, another BLANK Information sheet, and detailed information on the MINOR Countries involved during this period of Military conflict.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Scenarios included with this are: &amp;#10;S-21.The Battle of Austerlitz-Dec.2,1805; &amp;#10;S-22.The Battle of Vimiero-Aug.21,1808; &amp;#10;S-23.The Battle of Wagram-July 6,1809; &amp;#10;S-24.The Battle of Albuera-May 16, 1811; &amp;#10;S-25.The Battle of Lutzen-May 2,1813.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The S-23.Wagram Scenario has 4-(!) tables being used for it's playing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are massive amounts of detail included with this concerning the Leaders &amp;amp; Commanders of just about every Nation or Minor country involved during the entire Campaigns of Napoleon! I'll add that they've incorrectly listed Scenarios 24~26 as they 'skipped' #23 but there are still 5 more of them and are listed correctly in the Table of Contents.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
